title: Kara and Nate
description:
Hey, y'all! We are a husband and wife from Nashville, Tennessee. 

We started our YouTube channel on a whim when we decided to take a year off and go travel back in 2016. One year quickly turned into 4, and at the very end of 2019 we stepped foot in our 100th country. If you want a quick summary of that journey you can watch the documentary here - https://bit.ly/41TbOKJ

Shortly after achieving our 100 country goal, the pandemic hit. With international travel no longer an option, we bought a van and spent 2 years traveling around the U.S. living in our tiny home on wheels. At the beginning of 2022, we moved out of the van and back into our suitcases full-time. We're not exactly sure what our next "goal" is going to be, but we're currently having fun bouncing around the globe chasing our passions & interesting stories.

What is Sarcasm?
Sarcasm is saying something, but meaning the opposite ‚Äî often to highlight absurdity or make a point sharper. At A2D, we use sarcasm to cut through hype and expose reality in  tech, finance & business discussions. But without recognizing the tone, it can be misunderstood as serious. Context gives meaning. Without it, facts can mislead and opinions can be misunderstood. At A2D, we tackle complex and sometimes controversial tech, finance, business topics. title: Mrs Midwest
description:
Hello and welcome to my little piece of the Internet!

My name is Caitlin and I run the blog called "Mrs. Midwest." I joined YouTube in 2019 with the goal of creating a haven for traditionally feminine women trying to find their place in this modern world. Being a traditional homemaker and wife myself, it is my aim to help women blossom into their natural femininity through discussions on style, mindset, and relationships.

Our community of #femininewomen is open to women of all walks of life, yet we are ultimately here to amplify the voice of traditionally feminine women and their respective lifestyles. We explore topics relating to elegance, femininity, traditional relationships, and homemaking, with a little bit of my "real" life thrown in. 

I am open to partnerships if the shoe fits, but my main goal for this channel will always be to help women blossom into their best, most feminine selves! 

Thanks for visiting, and stay fresh! 

xoxo,


Cait

title: The Food Ranger
description:
My name is Trevor James and I live to eat and travel.  I live for street food and local food, and I'm traveling to taste it. I'm a hungry traveler that's currently living abroad in Chengdu, Sichuan China,  eating as much delicious food as I can.

So far, I've eaten and filmed street food and local cuisine in China, Malaysia, Singapore, and Thailand. Eating the same food as local Chinese, Malaysian, or Thai people has showed me that it's best to travel almost solely for the food! My dream is to keep eating and traveling the world forever, a non-stop adventure!  I live to travel, and I know you do too! I love eating street foods and culinary treats while learning about new cultures!

Food is different around the world, and I want to share it with you. Food is something that connects us all, and to me, food is the best way to connect and have a true cultural experience!

for business inquires: thefoodranger@delkatalents.com

description:
we make videos...

What is Sarcasm?
Sarcasm is saying something, but meaning the opposite ‚Äî often to highlight absurdity or make a point sharper. At A2D, we use sarcasm to cut through hype and expose reality in  tech, finance & business discussions. But without recognizing the tone, it can be misunderstood as serious. Sarcasm, when understood, adds humor and clarity; when missed, it creates confusion. That‚Äôs why spotting sarcasm is key to truly getting the message.

Why Context Matters?
Context gives meaning. Without it, facts can mislead and opinions can be misunderstood. At A2D, we tackle complex and sometimes controversial tech, finance, business topics. Without grasping the background and intent, our content may be misjudged. Context connects the "what" with the "why," ensuring clarity and fairness in every discussion.

description:
Hey, y'all! We are a husband and wife from Nashville, Tennessee. 

We started our YouTube channel on a whim when we decided to take a year off and go travel back in 2016. If you want a quick summary of that journey you can watch the documentary here - https://bit.ly/41TbOKJ

Shortly after achieving our 100 country goal, the pandemic hit. With international travel no longer an option, we bought a van and spent 2 years traveling around the U.S. living in our tiny home on wheels. At the beginning of 2022, we moved out of the van and back into our suitcases full-time. title: Mrs Midwest
description:
Hello and welcome to my little piece of the Internet!

My name is Caitlin and I run the blog called "Mrs. Midwest." I joined YouTube in 2019 with the goal of creating a haven for traditionally feminine women trying to find their place in this modern world. Being a traditional homemaker and wife myself, it is my aim to help women blossom into their natural femininity through discussions on style, mindset, and relationships.

Our community of #femininewomen is open to women of all walks of life, yet we are ultimately here to amplify the voice of traditionally feminine women and their respective lifestyles. We explore topics relating to elegance, femininity, traditional relationships, and homemaking, with a little bit of my "real" life thrown in. 

I am open to partnerships if the shoe fits, but my main goal for this channel will always be to help women blossom into their best, most feminine selves! 

Thanks for visiting, and stay fresh! 

xoxo,


Cait

title: The Food Ranger
description:
My name is Trevor James and I live to eat and travel.  I live for street food and local food, and I'm traveling to taste it. I'm a hungry traveler that's currently living abroad in Chengdu, Sichuan China,  eating as much delicious food as I can.

So far, I've eaten and filmed street food and local cuisine in China, Malaysia, Singapore, and Thailand. Eating the same food as local Chinese, Malaysian, or Thai people has showed me that it's best to travel almost solely for the food! My dream is to keep eating and traveling the world forever, a non-stop adventure!  I live to travel, and I know you do too! title: Wayne Dyer Motivation
description: Wayne Walter Dyer (May 10, 1940 ‚Äì August 29, 2015) was an American self-help author and a motivational speaker. Dyer completed a Ed.D. in guidance and counseling at Wayne State University in 1970. He became a popular professor of counselor education at St. John's University, where he was approached by a literary agent to put his ideas into book form. The result was his first book, Your Erroneous Zones (1976), one of the best-selling books of all time. This launched Dyer's career as a motivational speaker and self-help author, during which he published 20 more best-selling books and produced a number of popular specials for PBS. Dyer's early work focused on psychological themes such as motivation, self actualization and assertiveness. By the 1990s, the focus of his work had shifted to spirituality.

title: Sean Tucker
description:
I‚Äôm more interested in the ‚Äòwhy‚Äô of photography than in the ‚Äòhow‚Äô. 

There are loads of channels out there enthusiastically giving you gear reviews and top ten lists, but that's not this channel. 

There will be practical tips along the way, but the meat of what I want to share with you won't be tech heavy.

Besides, I believe that a photographer who really sees, but has a cheap camera; will produce better images than a photographer with the best gear, but no vision... every time.

I‚Äôm not a daily vlogger, I‚Äôm not even a weekly one. The most I can manage at the moment is about once a month. But that also means that I‚Äôm not going to fill this channel with repeats of other info online, or attempt to stretch a little bit of content a long way. 

I want every video to feel fresh and rich. 

Hopefully that makes them worth the wait.

title: Yasi Photography
description:
Hello and Welcome! 
A brief summary, I started this channel as a way to advertise myself as a photographer, and then I started vlogging, and then panini. Lost my way, retired, got hacked, lost my instagram, started Tiktok and now I am finding joy in the little moments. I don't exactly know where I am going with this channel but I do know that I will share whatever brings me joy. Restarting my business, books, editing, and going back to my roots in photography. I put so much joy and effort into my work, time and effort that I am no longer accepting defeat. I am back, and plan on staying here. Unafraid of taking up space and making it my own.
